reviews.text: Two ticket machines availiable for easy ticket buying, you can also talk to people inside for tickets. There are vending machines and a little shop for snacks. Overall not great but not bad either.

Nice enough station for the most part but why do Thameslink services go here? What was wrong with Gillingham? All the extra platform does is cut into the already restricted car parking space. At least the station has a decent amount of services here and step free access to all of the platforms.
Helpful staff and high speed service  to London isn't bad.

Rainham - 21/1/2018

Rainy Rainham. Summened this place up quite well really. I now know why I have never visited. I cant recommend and definitely not a place to go.on a wet Sunday.

The good;
Plenty of parking.
The cricketers looked half decent.

The bad;
Nothing really open. Although it was Sunday.
Feels like it's bigger brother Gillingham.
Lots of traffic on high street.
Not a great deal in thier shopping centre.
The station is very tired and in need of modernisation. It has  coffee shop coffee.e newsagents. 3 tickets will dowsing and 2 ticket machines.  Staff are always friendly though.
